{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2025-1916","published":"2025-08-01T13:02:27Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:31:46.950948Z","upstream":["CVE-2025-7519"],"summary":"polkit security update","details":"polkit is a toolkit for defining and handling authorizations. It is used for allowing unprivileged processes to speak to privileged processes.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nA flaw was found in polkit. When processing an XML policy with 32 or more nested elements in depth, an out-of-bounds write can be triggered. This issue can lead to a crash or other unexpected behavior, and arbitrary code execution is not discarded. To exploit this flaw, a high-privilege account is needed as it&apos;s required to place the malicious policy file properly.(CVE-2025-7519)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"polkit","ecosystem":"openEuler:24.03-LTS-SP2","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/polkit&distro=openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP2"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"123-2.oe2403sp2"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["polkit-123-2.oe2403sp2.aarch64.rpm","polkit-debuginfo-123-2.oe2403sp2.aarch64.rpm","polkit-debugsource-123-2.oe2403sp2.aarch64.rpm","polkit-devel-123-2.oe2403sp2.aarch64.rpm","polkit-libs-123-2.oe2403sp2.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["polkit-help-123-2.oe2403sp2.noarch.rpm"],"src":["polkit-123-2.oe2403sp2.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["polkit-123-2.oe2403sp2.x86_64.rpm","polkit-debuginfo-123-2.oe2403sp2.x86_64.rpm","polkit-debugsource-123-2.oe2403sp2.x86_64.rpm","polkit-devel-123-2.oe2403sp2.x86_64.rpm","polkit-libs-123-2.oe2403sp2.x86_64.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2025-1916.json"}}],"references":[{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://www.openeuler.org/zh/security/security-bulletins/detail/?id=openEuler-SA-2025-1916"},{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-7519"}],"database_specific":{"severity":"Medium"}}